This paper deals with distributed optimization, which is a topic that falls under machine learning and optimization. The paper discusses bias-correction methods, which are commonly used in machine learning algorithms to improve their performance. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the performance of these methods under stochastic and adaptive settings, which falls under the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also provides conditions for the superiority of exact diffusion over traditional algorithms, which falls under the sub-category of cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). The paper also discusses network topologies, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper provides simulations to validate the theoretical findings, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
